Shebang
The first line in python script files that tells the system where to locate the interpreter
#! /usr/bin/python3

Run a python program when it location is in pi or home folder and not in any sub folder
sudo python program _name.py
or
chmod +x program_name.py
./program_name.py 
or
(If you place them somewhere else than your home folder you will have to describe the whole path to start them)



